<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-429] Problem getting the HTTPClient to use HTTP 1.0 with a proxy server</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-429</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>I am using HTTPClient 3.0-rc1.&lt;br/&gt;
I am connecting to an HTTPS site through a proxy.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I used HTTPLook to see the HTTP messages between the Proxy and the HTTPClient.&lt;br/&gt;
I noticed that it always used HTTP/1.1 and setVersion() on either the &lt;br/&gt;
httpclient and the method do not help. I could not find how to get &lt;br/&gt;
the HTTPClient to use HTTP/1.0 with the proxy.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Looking at the ConnectMethod class, the HTTP1.1 was indeed hardcoded.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;br/&gt;
riad</description>
                <environment>Operating System: Windows 2000&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: PC</environment>
